args: Welcome back. Did you finish dealing\nwith your comrade?
All sinners are equally culpable in\nthe eyes of the Goddess, and must\nbe punishedâ€”whoever they are.
I'm glad to hear that. Still, you will have\nsome hard times ahead of you, now that\nthe apostles are one woman down.
That's our problem, not yours.\nNow where's this murdered priest?\nI need to inspect his corpse.
Whatever do you need to do that for?

No matter how much I questioned her,
I couldn't confirm our suspect did the deed.
I figured I might learn something new from
the body.
I'm afraid that won't be possible.\nThe victim has already been buried.
Then I guess I'd better get a shovel.
You would dare disturb the eternal\nrepose of the dead? Blasphemy, I say!
Is it? Or could it be that you don't want us\nfinding something that incriminates you?
Spare me your baseless accusations.\nI am simply a man of faith who will\nnot condone blasphemy.

See, I did a bit of digging on my own,
and I learned that a few months ago,
you suddenly became very negative
towards the apostles and angels.
Just what happened to you back then?\nActually, no. Let me cut right to the chase.
I hope you aren't implying someone\nordered me to do all of this to tarnish\nthe apostles' reputation.
The only thing I'm guilty of is witnessing\nyour friend murdering one of our priests.\nYou can prove nothing more.
A fair response. Without solid evidence,\nno one would believe us.
Hah. I'm glad you understand. If you want\nto pin a crime on me, you'd best be able\nto back up your claims!
YOU! How are you here?! You should be\ndead! Both he AND the Templars reported\nyou were sent flying off a cliff!
She wasâ€”but I never said she died from\nit. It'd take more than a little tumble like\nthat to finish her off.
Okay, I'm strong, but not THAT strong.\nI just got really lucky this time!

Curse you! Still, your luck ran out the
second you showed your face here.
You will atone for the murder of a
priest with your death!
I... I'm not the one who killed him!\nIt was YOU!
Ha ha ha. You're wasting your breath!\nEveryone has already accepted that\nthe murder was your doing.
You're going to need concrete evidence to\nconvince anyone that I was responsible!
Here's your evidence.\nHe told me everything.
Whaâ€”?! I mean, I've never met this\nman!
How could you say that, Father?!
Hah! You can't expect us to believe that\nwhen you're so visibly rattled.
After being sent flying off that cliff,\nI started looking for evidence that\nthe murder was your doing.
I was sure you'd destroyed all the physical\nevidence...but that still left the chance one\nof your friends could testify against you.
Although I only really started looking\ninto that possibility when Nevin and\nRamiel half-ordered me to.
We could hardly order you directly,\nknowing that we were being watched\nby the Templars.

If we'd been too obvious, we might've
been silenced. So we just...gave her a
little push. Figuratively AND literally,
in this case.
How were you both able to convey your\nintentions with such a brief exchange?!
I'm not all that smart,\nso I just did as I was told.
Nevin said I needed to look around for\nfriends who could help me.
I just took Raphael's message to mean\nthat I shouldn't give up as long as there\nare people who'd believe me, though.
And that message was the truth.\nSo? Who is our friend here?
I met him near a village I reached trying\nto shake off the Templars' pursuit.
I'm impressed you managed to work out\nthat he was in league with the bishop.
At first, I was thinking of picking a\nTemplar at random and tying them up.
But there was no telling how much they\neven knew. Plus, I could've just ended\nup getting chased around again.
That was when I remembered him.
I might have gone after him on instinct,\nbut I DID have reasons to suspect him.

He had the same smell of frankincense
as the church where I met the bishop,
and I heard him giving orders when
people surrounded the house I was at.
Neither stand as infallible evidence...but\nthey do make a convincing case for asking\nhim a few questions.
She did a LOT more than ask me a few\nquestions!
Because I'm so timid, I have a keen\neye for people's facial expressions.
I can tell what they fear the most,\nand what will hurt them the most.
Eeep... Don't look at me! PLEASE!
The heck did you do to this poor sod?
I really did just talk to him, I promise!\nHe told me that all of this was planned\nby the bishop.
His testimony proves you were the culprit!\nSo...please come quietly!
Don't listen to her, Templars!\nShe spews nothing but LIES!

The apostles are heretics who use the
Goddess's power to stain their hands
with blood! They and the angels should
be expelled from the Church at once!
Such caustic words. Whoever could\nhave gotten you thinking like that?
Kill the apostles AND the angel!\nWe can't let them have their way\nwith the Church!
*sigh* Show our stubborn friend the\nwill of the Goddess, you two.
I guess there's nothing else for it.
(Please, let me borrow a little of your\npower, Raphael.)
Bear witness to the Goddess's might!
